<TITLE> Thai trade fair begins Wednesday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May02 (bdnews24.com)  The four-day Thailand Trade Fair is set to start from Wednesday at Hotel Sonargaon in Dhaka. Jointly organised by Thailand and Bangladesh, the fair is expected to improve the commercial relations of the countries said Thai ambassador Tasanawadee Miancharoen at a conference. "It will also introduce the people of Bangladesh to the Thai culture." The fair will run from May 5 to May 8 and remain open to the public between 3pm to 8pm. Although not open to the public, the fair will have commercial exchanges and business deals among businesses from 10am to 3pm for the four days. The fair will house 47 companies that include agro-processors, chemical industries, electric products, garment, jewellery, shoes, etc. The fair has been organised to strengthen the trade relations between Bangladesh and Thailand and facilitate the exchange of cultures, said the president of Bangladesh-Thai Chamber of Commerce, MA Mamun. He also said trade between the countries amounted to some $650 million. "The target of this fair is to increase that trade." Apart from this, the Thai Food Exhibition will be held from May 5 and May 11, another joint venture with Hotel Sonargaon and Thailand at the same venue. 
